# Trivy CVE exception list.
# Format: CVE-ID  [expiry date]
#
# Each entry MUST have an inline comment documenting:
#   1. Why this CVE does not apply to this image/workload
#   2. An expiry date — force yourself to re-evaluate when the date passes
#
# Empty files are fine — it means all unfixed CVEs in the image are genuinely
# blocking and must be resolved or the pipeline fails.
#
# Example (commented out — uncomment and justify only if a real exception is needed):
#
# CVE-2023-XXXXX  exp:2024-06-01
# Reason: affects the bash shell; our distroless image has no shell,
#         so this CVE cannot be exploited in our environment.
